1
00:00:11,920 --> 00:00:13,098
Umm...

2
00:00:13,188 --> 00:00:14,892
Could you...

3
00:00:14,978 --> 00:00:17,268
Return the photocopy?

4
00:00:17,777 --> 00:00:18,798
Huh?

5
00:00:18,857 --> 00:00:20,128
Photocopy?

6
00:00:20,208 --> 00:00:21,938
Aye...

7
00:00:35,630 --> 00:00:40,058
'He thinks I've fallen for him'...

8
00:00:41,588 --> 00:00:43,678
'The poor prat'!

9
00:00:53,340 --> 00:00:56,129
'If this be love, dear'...

10
00:00:58,080 --> 00:00:59,680
'May you'

11
00:00:59,771 --> 00:01:02,131
'Groan in agony'...

12
00:01:03,650 --> 00:01:05,391
'"Amour"' (Love),

13
00:01:05,790 --> 00:01:08,610
'"Je te déteste"' (I hate you)...

14
00:01:14,090 --> 00:01:15,768
Here's your

15
00:01:15,830 --> 00:01:17,688
Photocopy...

16
00:01:25,820 --> 00:01:27,268
Feel free

17
00:01:27,268 --> 00:01:28,378
To let me know

18
00:01:28,378 --> 00:01:30,968
If you need anything.

19
00:01:47,080 --> 00:01:48,178
Hello?

20
00:01:48,178 --> 00:01:50,208
Give your Mum the phone.

21
00:01:50,248 --> 00:01:51,692
Ammi Begum?

22
00:01:51,753 --> 00:01:54,414
Nah, Aunt May.

23
00:01:55,573 --> 00:01:58,888
Mum! It's Nano!

24
00:02:02,150 --> 00:02:03,457
Here.

25
00:02:08,830 --> 00:02:10,228
Yes, Ammi Begum?

26
00:02:10,228 --> 00:02:13,367
Mehrunnisa scoffed at me.

27
00:02:13,458 --> 00:02:14,758
Hey!

28
00:02:14,978 --> 00:02:16,498
Did it hurt you?

29
00:02:16,498 --> 00:02:18,609
I can't believe it!

30
00:02:18,669 --> 00:02:21,299
I can...

31
00:02:21,592 --> 00:02:25,013
When an otherwise-duteous daughter-in-law scoffs at you...

32
00:02:25,085 --> 00:02:30,622
The mother-in-law should admit she's ruined everything.

33
00:02:30,732 --> 00:02:32,382
What are you saying?

34
00:02:32,382 --> 00:02:34,992
I didn't give in before her.

35
00:02:35,057 --> 00:02:39,377
I blamed everything on the blighter!

36
00:02:40,740 --> 00:02:42,898
But Suraiyya,

37
00:02:43,738 --> 00:02:46,317
She's got a point.

38
00:02:46,820 --> 00:02:48,088
What?

39
00:02:48,088 --> 00:02:49,828
I...

40
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:54,370
Broke too many hearts to keep my word...

41
00:02:56,328 --> 00:02:58,808
That actually you, Ammi Begum?

42
00:02:58,888 --> 00:03:00,338
Nah,

43
00:03:00,418 --> 00:03:03,010
It's your Aunt May!

44
00:03:03,180 --> 00:03:04,929
Honestly?

45
00:03:05,979 --> 00:03:08,859
I don't get it.

46
00:03:09,929 --> 00:03:11,904
Last night...

47
00:03:13,179 --> 00:03:16,140
I saw it myself.

48
00:03:17,389 --> 00:03:21,579
I saw just how much they love each other.

49
00:03:24,410 --> 00:03:26,228
They'd

50
00:03:26,500 --> 00:03:29,518
Die if separated.

51
00:03:33,540 --> 00:03:37,588
I'd been cruel to you once...

52
00:03:38,618 --> 00:03:43,178
When I got you married to that wretched Aurangzeb...

53
00:03:44,168 --> 00:03:46,988
You took it quietly...

54
00:03:49,428 --> 00:03:53,299
But I wonder

55
00:03:54,558 --> 00:03:58,548
If Maheen would take it lying down too.

56
00:03:59,860 --> 00:04:01,350
But --

57
00:04:01,478 --> 00:04:02,869
I --

58
00:04:02,964 --> 00:04:10,101
How much longer can I make my family gulp down this poison? How much longer can I reign supreme?

59
00:04:10,958 --> 00:04:18,478
I've got to be fair for a change... Concede my defeat before love sometime...

60
00:04:19,789 --> 00:04:24,510
Got to admit that love - even between two twits -

61
00:04:24,573 --> 00:04:27,949
Dwarfs our authority.

62
00:04:28,648 --> 00:04:30,598
And Gulrez?

63
00:04:31,369 --> 00:04:32,788
What about him?

64
00:04:32,788 --> 00:04:35,350
What <i>about</i> him?

65
00:04:35,708 --> 00:04:39,430
It happens when love is one-sided...

66
00:04:39,978 --> 00:04:42,418
You get hunger, not food...

67
00:04:42,418 --> 00:04:43,859
Anyway, bye...

68
00:04:43,939 --> 00:04:46,159
Hang up already! I'm tearing up!

69
00:04:46,159 --> 00:04:47,598
And --

70
00:04:47,658 --> 00:04:50,208
I'm crying for the one

71
00:04:50,289 --> 00:04:53,609
I'd slapped hard last night.

72
00:04:54,379 --> 00:04:55,970
For real?

73
00:04:55,970 --> 00:04:58,978
Can't you comfort me?

74
00:04:59,288 --> 00:05:03,588
Say I'm not all that bad?

75
00:05:05,580 --> 00:05:07,488
What are you saying?

76
00:05:07,488 --> 00:05:11,420
It's hard to find a mother and friend like you in the world.

77
00:05:11,450 --> 00:05:13,706
Thank you, Suraiyya.

78
00:05:14,050 --> 00:05:16,361
Thank you very much.

79
00:05:16,830 --> 00:05:19,175
You're speaking English?

80
00:05:19,301 --> 00:05:23,521
It's okay if you really have to, sometimes!

81
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:25,688
Now --

82
00:05:26,050 --> 00:05:28,110
Please hang up...

83
00:05:28,110 --> 00:05:30,979
Before he slips away.

84
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:56,351
Maheen...

85
00:06:00,050 --> 00:06:01,703
Maheen!

86
00:06:02,408 --> 00:06:04,079
Maheen?

87
00:06:14,279 --> 00:06:16,080
Where's Maheen?

88
00:06:16,861 --> 00:06:19,030
Gone to see someone.

89
00:06:19,780 --> 00:06:20,849
Who?

90
00:06:20,849 --> 00:06:22,409
Gulrez.

91
00:06:22,969 --> 00:06:24,660
Gulrez?

92
00:06:24,783 --> 00:06:25,719
Why?

93
00:06:25,719 --> 00:06:29,679
Waqar said he was just taking her for a ride last night.

94
00:06:29,725 --> 00:06:33,601
And that he doesn't really love her at all.

95
00:06:34,135 --> 00:06:36,840
So what's she gonna tell Gulrez?

96
00:06:36,870 --> 00:06:38,110
Anything.

97
00:06:38,171 --> 00:06:42,420
Perhaps even tell him everything and say... 'Good riddance'!

98
00:06:42,510 --> 00:06:43,701
Good riddance?

99
00:06:43,701 --> 00:06:47,811
Good riddance of someone who couldn't appreciate how much he's loved!

100
00:06:47,871 --> 00:06:50,670
I say, don't stop her.

101
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:52,979
Let her have it her way.

102
00:06:53,068 --> 00:06:55,348
She said as she left,

103
00:06:55,429 --> 00:06:57,330
'Love's pointless'.

104
00:06:57,330 --> 00:06:59,908
'Matches are made in Heaven'.

105
00:06:59,956 --> 00:07:01,390
Stop her!

106
00:07:01,390 --> 00:07:04,360
Call her! Ammi Begum's given in!

107
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:07,035
As if it makes any difference.

108
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:11,420
The man she turned the engagement down for refused.

109
00:07:11,491 --> 00:07:14,850
She'd die but never marry him!

110
00:07:15,220 --> 00:07:17,328
Good Lord...

111
00:07:18,568 --> 00:07:20,158
Is he happy?

112
00:07:20,194 --> 00:07:22,158
The twit was lying!

113
00:07:22,158 --> 00:07:24,328
Someone must've told him to --

114
00:07:24,378 --> 00:07:27,289
Nobody told <i>her</i> to do anything though.

115
00:07:27,700 --> 00:07:28,938
Anyway...

116
00:07:30,048 --> 00:07:31,437
Forget it.

117
00:07:31,494 --> 00:07:35,178
Fix an auspicious date with Ammi Begum.

118
00:07:36,269 --> 00:07:38,488
After the call last night,

119
00:07:38,529 --> 00:07:40,193
Even I've accepted

120
00:07:40,235 --> 00:07:43,435
Gulrez as my brother-in-law to-be!

121
00:07:43,488 --> 00:07:45,698
Bless him, will you?

122
00:08:06,620 --> 00:08:08,978
Why are you so quiet?

123
00:08:10,990 --> 00:08:12,708
Have some?

124
00:08:16,370 --> 00:08:17,880
Good news.

125
00:08:17,880 --> 00:08:20,398
The tramp from London refused.

126
00:08:20,398 --> 00:08:22,417
He ain't marrying me!

127
00:08:24,210 --> 00:08:25,628
Oh?

128
00:08:26,211 --> 00:08:28,281
This ain't good news for me.

129
00:08:28,313 --> 00:08:29,562
Hey!

130
00:08:30,813 --> 00:08:32,905
I'd call it bad news.

131
00:08:34,820 --> 00:08:37,538
The separation of lovers

132
00:08:37,648 --> 00:08:39,848
Makes the ground tremble.

133
00:08:40,038 --> 00:08:42,098
Like an earthquake!

134
00:08:42,818 --> 00:08:46,770
And - who knows - that's why the ground's gonna break on Doomsday.

135
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:49,728
Oh please. Nothing's gonna happen!

136
00:08:49,788 --> 00:08:51,850
He doesn't even love me!

137
00:08:51,850 --> 00:08:55,638
He swore before Nano, Uncle, Aunt, and Munshi Alam!

138
00:08:55,698 --> 00:08:57,858
He was lying.

139
00:08:58,468 --> 00:09:00,860
Someone made him say it.

140
00:09:00,973 --> 00:09:03,769
I'd like this 'someone' to try me!

141
00:09:05,379 --> 00:09:09,909
You take a while to appreciate the solemn vows of love.

142
00:09:10,329 --> 00:09:12,068
What was that?

143
00:09:12,188 --> 00:09:13,858
Lovers

144
00:09:13,858 --> 00:09:16,489
Are given to pitying.

145
00:09:18,799 --> 00:09:21,109
He had pity on me.

146
00:09:21,548 --> 00:09:22,788
Splendid!

147
00:09:22,863 --> 00:09:24,718
Hear that, Neelam?

148
00:09:24,798 --> 00:09:26,580
He's bewitched!

149
00:09:26,670 --> 00:09:28,517
Absolutely.

150
00:09:29,333 --> 00:09:31,413
Only a true sorcerer

151
00:09:31,451 --> 00:09:35,810
Could sacrifice his love for his corrival and say he's leaving for London.

152
00:09:35,810 --> 00:09:37,308
He's leaving for London?

153
00:09:37,308 --> 00:09:39,498
If he didn't already.

154
00:09:39,608 --> 00:09:41,419
In fact, it's essential

155
00:09:41,419 --> 00:09:44,008
For his spell to work!

156
00:09:47,460 --> 00:09:51,229
Well guess what, I've begun to loathe him!

157
00:09:55,210 --> 00:09:56,903
I know that.

158
00:09:59,370 --> 00:10:01,831
You blow hot and cold too often.

159
00:10:01,869 --> 00:10:03,559
One cold lie...

160
00:10:03,559 --> 00:10:06,229
And you got all hot-headed.

161
00:10:11,859 --> 00:10:13,980
But tell me...

162
00:10:15,199 --> 00:10:17,999
Even if he actually turned you down,

163
00:10:18,042 --> 00:10:21,119
Could that ever change love into loathing?

164
00:10:24,792 --> 00:10:27,259
You turned someone down too.

165
00:10:27,639 --> 00:10:29,979
On the day of the engagement.

166
00:10:30,265 --> 00:10:32,966
You refused to wear the ring.

167
00:10:35,540 --> 00:10:37,928
I don't loathe you one bit.

168
00:10:41,850 --> 00:10:44,732
Why is it that your love

169
00:10:44,790 --> 00:10:47,807
Grows to loathe your love so quickly?

170
00:10:55,550 --> 00:10:57,128
If you ask me...

171
00:10:57,182 --> 00:11:00,398
If that's how you define love,

172
00:11:02,738 --> 00:11:04,574
I'd loathe it too.

173
00:11:04,574 --> 00:11:07,618
Let her finish.
-I won't.

174
00:11:14,750 --> 00:11:17,079
I've been gravely wronged!

175
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:19,613
He had pity on me!

176
00:11:20,862 --> 00:11:25,641
There can be no greater insult than pitying a lover.

177
00:11:28,641 --> 00:11:30,731
I won't stay quiet.

178
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:33,620
I'll tell her everything.

179
00:11:33,980 --> 00:11:35,590
What?

180
00:11:36,380 --> 00:11:38,795
You called him over.

181
00:11:39,170 --> 00:11:41,950
Showed him my letters to Maheen.

182
00:11:42,002 --> 00:11:43,183
As in,

183
00:11:43,183 --> 00:11:46,063
Gave him reason to have pity.

184
00:11:46,743 --> 00:11:49,504
Swear by me if I'm lying.

185
00:11:49,606 --> 00:11:51,334
C'mon?

186
00:11:52,266 --> 00:11:55,026
I've burnt every single one of them.

187
00:11:55,305 --> 00:11:59,948
Charred my treasure to ashes because he had pity on me.

188
00:12:00,345 --> 00:12:03,906
That's how much it's hurt me.

189
00:12:04,226 --> 00:12:05,666
Look...

190
00:12:06,195 --> 00:12:08,371
How low I've fallen...

191
00:12:17,610 --> 00:12:19,901
It's Neelam's fault.

192
00:12:19,999 --> 00:12:21,979
She cried before him.

193
00:12:21,979 --> 00:12:24,469
He had mercy on me.

194
00:12:26,199 --> 00:12:28,070
So please, tell me...

195
00:12:28,700 --> 00:12:31,880
If someone had mercy on lovers,

196
00:12:31,910 --> 00:12:35,869
Which upright man out there would dare to fall in love?

197
00:12:38,139 --> 00:12:41,550
We don't hear much about love of late,

198
00:12:41,850 --> 00:12:43,909
So don't humiliate

199
00:12:43,909 --> 00:12:46,960
The rare man who's fallen in love.

200
00:13:03,540 --> 00:13:04,848
Hey...

201
00:13:10,820 --> 00:13:12,793
Promise me...

202
00:13:14,544 --> 00:13:16,008
Yeah?

203
00:13:17,948 --> 00:13:21,248
My Foxy's leading your wedding procession.

204
00:13:40,150 --> 00:13:42,209
I swear by you.

205
00:13:43,330 --> 00:13:46,480
Your Foxy's gonna lead my wedding procession.

206
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:47,541
Your Foxy's gonna lead my wedding procession.
