♪ <i>That those we hold dear to us are the ones who break our heart</i> ♪

214
00:14:59,457 --> 00:15:10,040
♪ <i>That those we hold dear to us are the ones who break our heart...</i> ♪

215
00:15:49,250 --> 00:15:51,377
I feel so guilty, Jiya.

216
00:15:51,738 --> 00:15:54,628
I love Maheen so much, but...

217
00:15:55,508 --> 00:15:58,048
I don't want to marry her.

218
00:15:58,580 --> 00:16:00,438
Why not?

219
00:16:01,790 --> 00:16:03,769
Poor little Gulrez...

220
00:16:03,929 --> 00:16:06,679
He loves her much more than I ever can.

221
00:16:06,980 --> 00:16:08,478
So?

222
00:16:10,151 --> 00:16:11,668
What?

223
00:16:15,670 --> 00:16:17,728
I'm afraid

224
00:16:17,900 --> 00:16:19,600
He may die

225
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:22,139
On the day of our wedding.

226
00:16:24,589 --> 00:16:26,969
Talk about Maheen.

227
00:16:27,948 --> 00:16:30,358
Who does she love?

228
00:16:31,592 --> 00:16:33,979
She never said it, but...

229
00:16:35,199 --> 00:16:38,009
I know there's something between us.

230
00:16:38,828 --> 00:16:41,108
The way she called and stopped me...

231
00:16:41,108 --> 00:16:43,949
It felt like if I didn't turn back...

232
00:16:44,308 --> 00:16:45,849
She'd die.

233
00:16:45,849 --> 00:16:47,919
No one's gonna die.

234
00:16:49,248 --> 00:16:50,519
I mean --

235
00:16:50,688 --> 00:16:54,994
You can't be serious! He's gonna die, she's gonna die...

236
00:16:55,180 --> 00:16:58,684
Just think about your life!

237
00:16:59,558 --> 00:17:01,348
I have.

238
00:17:02,258 --> 00:17:05,588
Sometimes, I think that without Maheen...

239
00:17:05,930 --> 00:17:07,928
I'd die...

240
00:17:09,828 --> 00:17:12,598
That leads me to think how he...

241
00:17:13,850 --> 00:17:17,518
He's written hundreds of letters to Maheen in these ten years.

242
00:17:18,869 --> 00:17:21,209
He burnt them all because of me.

243
00:17:21,349 --> 00:17:24,134
Now, he's holding on to the ashes...

244
00:17:25,230 --> 00:17:29,310
How does he have the letters he wrote to Maheen?

245
00:17:29,430 --> 00:17:31,838
He never sent them.

246
00:17:32,750 --> 00:17:35,188
He could never bring himself to.

247
00:17:35,510 --> 00:17:40,081
He'd write them, go through them, and think he'd told Maheen everything.

248
00:17:40,241 --> 00:17:41,931
Wow...

249
00:17:44,101 --> 00:17:47,271
He never asked me to get out of the way.

250
00:17:48,274 --> 00:17:51,041
He got out of the way for me.

251
00:17:56,300 --> 00:17:58,040
What's so funny?

252
00:18:04,280 --> 00:18:08,268
Who's the Gang Chief these days?

253
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:10,029
Please, Jiya...

254
00:18:10,098 --> 00:18:12,279
I'm very serious.

255
00:18:12,321 --> 00:18:14,281
I'm very serious too.

256
00:18:14,281 --> 00:18:16,421
Who's the Chief?

257
00:18:16,610 --> 00:18:17,959
Maheen.

258
00:18:17,989 --> 00:18:20,528
Maheen Aurangzeb.

259
00:18:20,924 --> 00:18:24,248
And is he in the Gang too? Gulrez?

260
00:18:24,859 --> 00:18:25,969
Maybe...

261
00:18:25,969 --> 00:18:27,800
But it's so irrelevant.

262
00:18:28,040 --> 00:18:30,471
Perhaps... Perhaps not?

263
00:18:30,970 --> 00:18:32,428
I mean...

264
00:18:33,370 --> 00:18:36,678
Maheen's my best friend...

265
00:18:37,287 --> 00:18:41,417
She never told me she loves you.

266
00:18:41,736 --> 00:18:42,657
Aye,

267
00:18:42,657 --> 00:18:44,558
She always said,

268
00:18:44,558 --> 00:18:47,520
'I'll teach him a lesson',

269
00:18:47,520 --> 00:18:49,898
'I'll make him pay for the slap',

270
00:18:49,898 --> 00:18:54,769
'Settle the scores', 'kill him off where he won't find any relief'... Stuff like that...

271
00:18:56,300 --> 00:18:59,089
She says that when she's furious.

272
00:19:00,468 --> 00:19:02,468
Your problem is not

273
00:19:02,518 --> 00:19:05,468
How much Gulrez loves her.

274
00:19:08,150 --> 00:19:10,430
Your problem

275
00:19:10,623 --> 00:19:12,902
Is you believe

276
00:19:12,942 --> 00:19:14,942
She loves you.

277
00:19:16,692 --> 00:19:17,972
What?

278
00:19:18,420 --> 00:19:20,428
What d'you mean?

279
00:19:20,970 --> 00:19:24,868
You think it's completely irrelevant, don't you?

280
00:19:24,918 --> 00:19:28,789
You'd do well to make sure.

281
00:19:29,559 --> 00:19:31,759
What? Make sure of what?

282
00:19:32,930 --> 00:19:35,092
It's so simple, Waqar.

283
00:19:35,268 --> 00:19:38,608
Let her say she loves you.

284
00:19:39,738 --> 00:19:41,698
You don't know her.

285
00:19:41,848 --> 00:19:43,878
She'd never say that.

286
00:19:45,910 --> 00:19:47,936
I know her, Waqar.

287
00:19:48,001 --> 00:19:50,841
She'd never say that.

288
00:19:51,466 --> 00:19:56,768
That's why I say, don't think your Gang's irrelevant.

289
00:19:57,221 --> 00:19:58,532
Maybe

290
00:19:58,532 --> 00:20:00,681
I'm wrong about it,

291
00:20:00,971 --> 00:20:02,232
But

292
00:20:02,232 --> 00:20:05,201
You should not take any chances.

293
00:20:16,130 --> 00:20:19,038
Granted, she's got quite the ego...

294
00:20:19,868 --> 00:20:21,208
But

295
00:20:21,278 --> 00:20:23,459
Sacrificing her love

296
00:20:23,608 --> 00:20:26,279
With her silence?

297
00:20:30,440 --> 00:20:32,038
Impossible.

298
00:21:03,650 --> 00:21:06,748
Looking at Gulrez pains me.

299
00:21:07,318 --> 00:21:11,498
Hearing him, you'd think he isn't even from this world.

300
00:21:13,088 --> 00:21:14,899
He doesn't love me.

301
00:21:14,958 --> 00:21:16,839
He worships me.

302
00:21:17,093 --> 00:21:18,968
But I can't help it.

303
00:21:19,010 --> 00:21:22,609
His love and devotion are no good to me.

304
00:21:22,978 --> 00:21:25,638
The twit's not really my type.

305
00:21:29,019 --> 00:21:31,420
But the one I hated for all these years,

306
00:21:31,420 --> 00:21:34,982
The one I planned to get even with when he'd come back...

307
00:21:35,019 --> 00:21:37,533
I can't settle any score with him.

308
00:21:37,630 --> 00:21:40,260
Not when I've fallen for him.

309
00:21:45,900 --> 00:21:48,550
Can't believe it's happening, but it's real...

310
00:21:48,580 --> 00:21:50,320
Good Lord...

311
00:21:56,999 --> 00:22:00,590
If he didn't hear my call and turn back,

312
00:22:00,669 --> 00:22:03,379
I swear it would've killed me.

313
00:22:34,980 --> 00:22:38,758
Who's the Gang Chief these days?

314
00:22:38,808 --> 00:22:41,338
Perhaps it's not so irrelevant?

315
00:22:42,200 --> 00:22:44,878
Maheen's my best friend...

316
00:22:44,878 --> 00:22:48,848
She never told me she loves you.

317
00:22:49,700 --> 00:22:51,758
Why don't you tell 'em everything?

318
00:22:51,802 --> 00:22:54,142
Say those fiery words

319
00:22:54,212 --> 00:22:56,940
And shatter my ego for Nano to see!

320
00:22:56,940 --> 00:22:58,728
Aye, she always said,

321
00:22:58,728 --> 00:23:01,679
'I'll teach him a lesson',

322
00:23:01,679 --> 00:23:04,169
'I'll make him pay for the slap'...

323
00:23:26,350 --> 00:23:28,670
Sorry for disturbing you.

324
00:23:28,920 --> 00:23:30,800
It's okay.

325
00:23:31,360 --> 00:23:32,950
Grab a pew.

326
00:23:37,529 --> 00:23:39,423
So... What is it?

327
00:23:39,921 --> 00:23:43,920
You gotta write the last page for me.

328
00:23:45,590 --> 00:23:46,978
Hmm?

329
00:23:49,169 --> 00:23:50,758
Just one?

330
00:23:52,168 --> 00:23:53,550
Aye.

331
00:23:53,908 --> 00:23:55,519
Give me your draft.

332
00:23:55,564 --> 00:23:58,770
I haven't got a draft this time.

333
00:24:00,399 --> 00:24:02,268
I'll dictate.

334
00:24:02,268 --> 00:24:04,160
You write.

335
00:24:05,140 --> 00:24:07,348
Okay... No problem.

336
00:24:22,370 --> 00:24:23,969
Write down...

337
00:24:26,580 --> 00:24:28,988
'Everything went'

338
00:24:30,910 --> 00:24:33,879
'As we'd planned'...

339
00:24:34,651 --> 00:24:36,644
Just a minute...

340
00:24:38,100 --> 00:24:41,180
Lemme take a look at the previous pages...

341
00:24:41,590 --> 00:24:44,630
You took the samples with you.

342
00:24:44,850 --> 00:24:48,340
I need a moment to study the handwriting.

343
00:24:50,230 --> 00:24:51,573
Okay...

344
00:24:51,950 --> 00:24:53,667
Take your time.

345
00:25:11,630 --> 00:25:13,598
Uncle Qutb!

346
00:25:14,490 --> 00:25:16,541
Uncle Qutb!

347
00:25:22,510 --> 00:25:25,840
I've been screamin' at the top of my lungs! Can't you hear me?

348
00:25:25,840 --> 00:25:29,168
Do I look like Qutb?

349
00:25:29,168 --> 00:25:32,338
Want something? Go to the kitchen.

350
00:25:32,387 --> 00:25:34,858
I'm too busy with my studies.

351
00:25:36,240 --> 00:25:38,168
Where's Uncle Qutb?

352
00:25:39,028 --> 00:25:40,888
With Mum.

353
00:25:41,158 --> 00:25:42,878
And where's Mum?

354
00:25:42,914 --> 00:25:44,585
At Nano's.

355
00:25:45,854 --> 00:25:47,435
At 1 a.m.?

356
00:25:47,468 --> 00:25:51,259
Nano's orders. 'Come at once if convenient. If inconvenient come all the same'.

357
00:25:51,259 --> 00:25:55,358
Uncle Qutb drove her because the driver's wife's sick.

358
00:25:55,418 --> 00:25:57,169
Anything else?

359
00:25:59,944 --> 00:26:02,454
You better have something.

360
00:26:04,386 --> 00:26:05,626
Why?

361
00:26:05,717 --> 00:26:10,878
Who knows, the news from there may kill your hunger!

362
00:26:11,118 --> 00:26:16,419
I've got nothing to fear. Gulrez ain't marrying me even if they all begged him.

363
00:26:16,589 --> 00:26:18,993
You'd die for that London tramp, wouldn't you?

364
00:26:18,993 --> 00:26:20,440
Can it!

365
00:26:20,540 --> 00:26:22,815
To the dickens with him!

366
00:26:32,670 --> 00:26:34,958
We're out of options...

367
00:26:35,928 --> 00:26:40,109
Anger's not gonna do any good... Nor will soothing anyone...

368
00:26:43,470 --> 00:26:46,288
The point, plainly,

369
00:26:46,707 --> 00:26:49,909
Is that Gulrez is out of the picture.

370
00:26:55,180 --> 00:26:58,908
My sweet Fatima's poor wee lad...

371
00:27:01,940 --> 00:27:03,978
Go on...

372
00:27:06,490 --> 00:27:08,308
About?

373
00:27:10,490 --> 00:27:13,619
They've both proven

374
00:27:13,760 --> 00:27:18,558
That Kaneez Begum is moron number one.

375
00:27:22,260 --> 00:27:23,899
So...

376
00:27:24,308 --> 00:27:29,253
You three get to decide and tell me this time.

377
00:27:29,348 --> 00:27:31,473
No way, Ammi Begum.

378
00:27:31,568 --> 00:27:33,839
You get to decide.

379
00:27:35,940 --> 00:27:38,118
Why don't you say anything?

380
00:27:38,168 --> 00:27:43,079
You're listening quietly as if we're talking about the neighbour's girl.

381
00:27:44,080 --> 00:27:46,488
I've lost, Ammi Begum.

382
00:27:47,310 --> 00:27:50,999
No one asked for your confession.

383
00:27:52,167 --> 00:27:53,828
Confession?

384
00:27:55,917 --> 00:27:58,078
I told you...

385
00:27:58,291 --> 00:28:02,422
No big deal speaking English when you really need to...

386
00:28:04,491 --> 00:28:06,880
Back to business...

387
00:28:06,971 --> 00:28:08,721
Okay...

388
00:28:08,940 --> 00:28:11,252
As it pleases the Lord.

389
00:28:12,740 --> 00:28:14,141
As in?

390
00:28:15,720 --> 00:28:19,751
If we can't take up arms against love...

391
00:28:20,390 --> 00:28:22,111
There's one...

392
00:28:22,331 --> 00:28:24,390
Against two...

393
00:28:27,370 --> 00:28:29,320
The one...

394
00:28:30,414 --> 00:28:33,851
Is entirely one-sided... Always has been...

395
00:28:41,760 --> 00:28:45,641
Ration me rum if I understood a word Mehrunnisa just said.

396
00:28:45,810 --> 00:28:48,031
Spiffing...

397
00:28:49,580 --> 00:28:51,908
Get up.

398
00:28:52,028 --> 00:28:56,605
Go ask Munshi Alam to get us all a cuppa.

399
00:29:02,650 --> 00:29:04,218
Go on.

400
00:29:04,640 --> 00:29:07,148
Are you happy with the proposal?

401
00:29:07,247 --> 00:29:11,958
You wouldn't say you can't face Gulrez, would you?

402
00:29:14,330 --> 00:29:17,389
She's talking about Waqar and Maheen.

403
00:29:22,190 --> 00:29:24,496
Why are you still here?

404
00:29:24,577 --> 00:29:28,877
This ain't for you. Go.

405
00:29:32,870 --> 00:29:35,059
Go on, Suraiyya.

406
00:29:35,199 --> 00:29:40,259
Say you accept it or that you will stand by your word to your sister.

407
00:29:43,219 --> 00:29:45,979
I can't stand by my word, Ammi Begum...

408
00:29:47,029 --> 00:29:49,110
You're right...

409
00:29:49,760 --> 00:29:52,719
Gulrez is out of the picture.

410
00:29:54,730 --> 00:29:58,286
My sweet Fatima's poor wee lad...

411
00:30:00,420 --> 00:30:04,248
Please don't say that... It pains me so much...

412
00:30:04,248 --> 00:30:06,348
Don't stop me.

413
00:30:06,640 --> 00:30:10,010
I'll shed a few tears every time he'd face me...

414
00:30:10,010 --> 00:30:11,897
The poor lad...

415
00:30:12,180 --> 00:30:15,201
I can give him my blessings... And my sympathies...

416
00:30:15,290 --> 00:30:19,378
But his love's one-sided...

417
00:30:19,608 --> 00:30:22,180
I can't give him his love...

418
00:30:24,078 --> 00:30:27,389
She'd rather die for Waqar Ahmed...

419
00:30:47,440 --> 00:30:49,808
God be with ye.
-God be with ye.

420
00:30:52,300 --> 00:30:53,896
Neelam...

421
00:30:56,520 --> 00:30:58,398
Don't wake him up.

422
00:30:59,348 --> 00:31:02,087
Put him to sleep if he gets up.

423
00:31:04,360 --> 00:31:07,898
Ask him he's got to wait if he asks for breakfast.

424
00:31:08,648 --> 00:31:12,468
If he wants to go to work, stop him.

425
00:31:12,514 --> 00:31:14,178
Scold him if you must.

426
00:31:14,178 --> 00:31:16,239
But why?

427
00:31:16,469 --> 00:31:18,938
I've got my reasons.

428
00:31:19,308 --> 00:31:20,709
Care to tell me?

429
00:31:20,709 --> 00:31:22,238
I can't.

430
00:31:22,599 --> 00:31:24,738
But don't worry.

431
00:31:25,220 --> 00:31:27,899
It'll be out soon...

432
00:31:29,429 --> 00:31:31,779
You'll find out later today.

433
00:31:32,178 --> 00:31:34,869
I hope you've got sleeping pills...

434
00:31:35,038 --> 00:31:37,620
Give him one in his tea.

435
00:31:39,388 --> 00:31:41,038
What is it?

436
00:31:41,119 --> 00:31:43,233
It's nothing, really...

437
00:31:45,360 --> 00:31:46,680
Just...

438
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:49,308
My intuition...

439
00:31:50,290 --> 00:31:52,598
A gut feeling that warns me...

440
00:31:53,457 --> 00:31:55,438
About?

441
00:31:58,410 --> 00:32:00,858
I'd rather not want to say it.

442
00:32:04,390 --> 00:32:06,008
God be with ye.

443
00:32:20,610 --> 00:32:22,199
Peace be upon you, Nano.

444
00:32:22,264 --> 00:32:24,985
And upon you, peace.

445
00:32:25,794 --> 00:32:28,709
Had breakfast?

446
00:32:28,804 --> 00:32:30,224
No.

447
00:32:30,259 --> 00:32:32,104
Just sent Wali to work.

448
00:32:32,104 --> 00:32:33,760
Gulrez is sleeping.

449
00:32:33,760 --> 00:32:38,399
I'll have breakfast when he gets up. We eat together.

450
00:32:38,399 --> 00:32:39,825
Okay...

451
00:32:40,150 --> 00:32:42,348
I'll get back to you

452
00:32:42,508 --> 00:32:44,438
After breakfast.

453
00:32:44,498 --> 00:32:46,389
Please, go on.

454
00:32:46,520 --> 00:32:49,777
I don't want to wait until breakfast!

455
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:52,528
You'd better.

456
00:32:52,810 --> 00:32:56,138
Plus, that twit's sleeping...

457
00:32:56,348 --> 00:32:58,828
When he gets up, ask him

458
00:32:59,020 --> 00:33:01,768
If he can augur.

459
00:33:02,335 --> 00:33:03,828
Augur?

460
00:33:04,058 --> 00:33:07,978
Back in our day, we could.

461
00:33:08,558 --> 00:33:11,872
We may not love as much...

462
00:33:12,138 --> 00:33:15,409
But we'd augur much more... But it seems now...

463
00:33:15,473 --> 00:33:17,724
What is there to augur about?

464
00:33:17,900 --> 00:33:19,748
What is it, Nano?

465
00:33:19,958 --> 00:33:22,588
How do I tell you, love?

466
00:33:23,678 --> 00:33:26,214
Wali's not around...

467
00:33:26,920 --> 00:33:29,411
Gulrez's asleep...

468
00:33:29,770 --> 00:33:32,380
You're out there all alone...

469
00:33:33,380 --> 00:33:36,090
What if something happened to you?

470
00:33:36,298 --> 00:33:38,087
Don't worry.

471
00:33:38,279 --> 00:33:41,579
I know you're brave.

472
00:33:41,950 --> 00:33:44,908
But bravery, my dear,

473
00:33:45,240 --> 00:33:48,198
Can only last so long.

474
00:33:49,168 --> 00:33:50,988
Tell me...

475
00:33:52,178 --> 00:33:55,038
When was the last time you cried?

476
00:33:56,448 --> 00:33:58,988
I don't cry now.

477
00:33:59,118 --> 00:34:02,118
You're off form, so to speak...

478
00:34:03,708 --> 00:34:07,544
In that case, you better have breakfast first...

479
00:34:07,778 --> 00:34:10,678
Get back to me when you've had breakfast.

480
00:34:10,739 --> 00:34:13,232
I'll tell you everything

481
00:34:13,580 --> 00:34:15,871
If the Lord wills thus...

482
00:34:45,610 --> 00:34:46,958
Hello?

483
00:34:47,817 --> 00:34:50,737
You're marrying Maheen to Waqar?

484
00:34:51,348 --> 00:34:53,338
Me sainted uncle...

485
00:34:54,029 --> 00:34:56,399
That's some fine augury...

486
00:34:56,920 --> 00:34:58,938
I mean, just think about it.

487
00:34:59,058 --> 00:35:02,328
It's that poor twit who loves her,

488
00:35:02,419 --> 00:35:05,039
But you're the one auguring.

489
00:35:05,850 --> 00:35:09,560
Because I love him, Nano.

490
00:35:10,711 --> 00:35:12,171
Look...

491
00:35:12,650 --> 00:35:15,250
You better not start crying now.

492
00:35:17,450 --> 00:35:20,098
Just think I'm helpless...

493
00:35:22,460 --> 00:35:28,897
No truth can conceal your grey-haired lies better than the truth of your helplessness...

494
00:35:31,250 --> 00:35:33,497
You're there, aren't you?

495
00:35:35,828 --> 00:35:37,108
Yeah.

496
00:35:37,698 --> 00:35:39,488
Promise me...

497
00:35:42,170 --> 00:35:44,909
You'll have your breakfast like nothing happened

498
00:35:47,290 --> 00:35:50,484
And tell him cheerfully, with a smile -

499
00:35:51,785 --> 00:35:52,996
'She' --

500
00:35:53,070 --> 00:35:58,868
'She didn't deserve your love... She wanted a loafer layabout like herself'!

501
00:36:00,178 --> 00:36:02,488
Aren't you sending us sweets?

502
00:36:04,950 --> 00:36:07,159
Wha -- Sweets?

503
00:36:08,028 --> 00:36:10,393
You're not brave either.

504
00:36:10,919 --> 00:36:12,990
You will need to be, Nano.

505
00:36:14,900 --> 00:36:17,981
Good news ain't good without sweets.

506
00:36:18,630 --> 00:36:20,729
Please, send us some.

507
00:36:21,448 --> 00:36:23,510
I'll wake Gulrez up.

508
00:36:23,638 --> 00:36:27,968
Hold your horses, Neelam, or he'll die under their weight!

509
00:36:28,098 --> 00:36:30,408
He's already dead.

510
00:36:30,810 --> 00:36:33,490
He gave his life without an ounce of fear.

511
00:36:33,730 --> 00:36:36,630
I'm just cross as two sticks to wonder

512
00:36:37,261 --> 00:36:40,950
Why he couldn't augur and see the writing on the wall at all!

513
00:36:41,000 --> 00:36:46,000
